WEBVTT

00:05.760 --> 00:09.160
I am very fixed about
how I dress, what I do,

00:09.240 --> 00:10.400
what I don't do.

00:10.800 --> 00:13.160
This is completely out of my comfort zone.

00:13.360 --> 00:16.400
I think I have about 15 minutes to panic.

00:52.920 --> 00:56.840
Hi, I'm your host and part-time
video call hater, Sapan Verma,

00:56.920 --> 00:59.920
and on today's episode,
we have two proud pet parents

01:00.000 --> 01:01.840
who love to give us some positive news.

01:02.400 --> 01:05.440
TV news anchor turned
Instagram journalist Faye D'souza

01:05.720 --> 01:08.600
and the daddy cool
of Indian comedy, Atul Khatri.

01:08.880 --> 01:10.200
Thank you so much for coming!

01:10.280 --> 01:13.840
My name is Atul Khatri
and I am 52 years old.

01:15.000 --> 01:16.800
Yeah, usually I get a clap around here.
Come on, come on.

01:19.520 --> 01:21.120
Because at the age of 52,

01:21.200 --> 01:23.720
I'm India's oldest
English stand-up comedian.

01:24.560 --> 01:26.000
No, no, I don't get a clap here.
It's only for the age.

01:27.800 --> 01:30.560
And doing stand-up comedy at
this age is very tough. It's very tough!

01:31.200 --> 01:32.200
No, it's not the talking part.

01:32.280 --> 01:34.800
You know, as we guys get older,
we can speak for hours.

01:37.080 --> 01:38.960
It's the damn standing part
which is a problem.

01:41.960 --> 01:43.360
I love my daughters.
I love my daughters

01:43.440 --> 01:46.960
and I thank God every day
for giving me two daughters, honestly!

01:47.360 --> 01:48.720
Because I couldn't have handled sons.

01:48.800 --> 01:51.440
Because I know bloody what a
rascal of a son I've been to my parents.

01:53.560 --> 01:56.280
And I think, after so many years,
I've figured my daughters out, you know.

01:56.480 --> 01:59.160
Once every two-three months,
take them to H&M and Zara for shopping.

02:00.040 --> 02:01.920
Once every two-three years,
upgrade their iPhones.

02:02.600 --> 02:04.600
Instagram accounts,
Snapchat accounts… set!

02:04.760 --> 02:06.320
Poor girls don't ask for anything more.

02:07.640 --> 02:10.640
Sons, bloody, right from the beginning,
they want your cycle, your motorcycle,

02:10.760 --> 02:12.000
your shoes, your belt,

02:12.120 --> 02:13.880
name in your property, career, will…

02:13.960 --> 02:15.040
It never ends!

02:17.440 --> 02:19.720
You've heard of sons
fighting over property, correct?

02:20.320 --> 02:22.960
My two daughters
fight over a 200-rupee kajal pencil.

02:26.560 --> 02:28.400
Last year, my elder daughter
came and told me, "Papa,

02:28.520 --> 02:31.040
I want to go for a
backpacking trip to Croatia."

02:31.680 --> 02:34.040
I said, "Amazing! First of all,
show me where Croatia is on the map."

02:36.160 --> 02:37.800
See, I have these two
simple rules with my daughter.

02:37.880 --> 02:39.880
If you have to go somewhere,
show me where it is on the map.

02:40.240 --> 02:43.040
And if you have to go to a music concert,
make me hear the lyrics.

02:43.600 --> 02:46.280
Because many years back, I went
with them to a Justin Bieber concert.

02:46.400 --> 02:47.680
And it was not what it promised to be.

02:51.680 --> 02:53.000
So, we have that globe at home.

02:53.080 --> 02:54.960
She looked for ten minutes,
but could not find Croatia there.

02:56.040 --> 02:58.040
Then she looked it up on Google maps,
it was close to Italy.

02:58.520 --> 03:01.240
I said, "Dear, why do you want to
go all the way to Croatia? So far away!"

03:01.520 --> 03:03.320
She's like,
"Dad, Croatia has got a lot of history!"

03:03.800 --> 03:05.440
I said, "What history does Croatia have?"

03:06.120 --> 03:07.960
She said, "Dad,
the Lannisters were born there!

03:09.600 --> 03:12.400
Cersei Lannister,
Jaime Lannister, Tyrion Lannister.

03:12.920 --> 03:14.960
Dad, the battle of Blackwater
Bay was fought there."

03:15.720 --> 03:17.760
Sir, I think you are lost.
It's a Game of Thrones reference.

03:18.760 --> 03:21.600
She said, "Dad,
book premium economy tickets for me."

03:21.720 --> 03:23.840
I said, "Bloody, you are going
backpacking. Fly economy."

03:23.960 --> 03:25.920
She said, "No, no, no.
I need extra legroom space."

03:26.120 --> 03:28.920
I said, "Dear, we're a family of hobbits.
We all have short legs."

03:30.720 --> 03:32.480
But I knew why it was called backpacking.

03:32.720 --> 03:35.160
Because of the amount of
money she spent on the trip,

03:35.640 --> 03:37.520
all I was left with was
a backpack of clothes on my shoulder.

03:37.600 --> 03:38.600
All my money was spent!

03:40.120 --> 03:41.800
Right, so what happened
at three o'clock in the morning,

03:41.880 --> 03:43.480
my elder daughter flew to Croatia.

03:43.840 --> 03:46.600
She stole the kajal pencil
from the dressing table, she flew off.

03:47.800 --> 03:50.360
In the morning, my younger daughter
got up, getting ready for college.

03:50.440 --> 03:52.720
She couldn't find the kajal pencil.
She knew she had stolen.

03:53.080 --> 03:54.680
She came banging into my room, "Dad!"

03:54.800 --> 03:55.680
I said, "What happened?"

03:55.760 --> 03:57.240
"Give me your phone!"
I said, "What's wrong?"

03:57.320 --> 03:59.600
"That <i>kutti</i> has taken
my kajal pencil to Croatia!"

04:04.040 --> 04:06.840
I'm like, "Mind your language!
It's not <i>kutti,</i> it's bitch!

04:10.000 --> 04:11.280
You can't mix two languages

04:11.360 --> 04:13.320
and you cannot call her to Croatia
using my phone!"

04:13.840 --> 04:15.560
She said, "No dad,
I don't have balance in my phone."

04:16.520 --> 04:18.480
This is a problem with every child.

04:19.040 --> 04:21.120
All day, when they're talking
to each other, they have enough balance.

04:21.320 --> 04:22.600
No balance for an important call!

04:23.240 --> 04:24.920
But see, I'm also old.
I've been through history.

04:25.320 --> 04:26.920
I know the divide
and rule policy, correct?

04:27.360 --> 04:28.520
So I said, "Good! Fight."

04:28.600 --> 04:30.080
I gave my phone and said,
"Fight with each other."

04:31.000 --> 04:33.560
And one thing I've seen, when
both my daughters fight with each other,

04:33.640 --> 04:35.000
they fight like cats and dogs.

04:35.560 --> 04:37.880
But if you scold one
child in front of the other,

04:38.240 --> 04:39.920
suddenly, they bloody gang up
like thieves.

04:41.920 --> 04:44.320
Suddenly, it's like Pakistan
and China against India…

04:45.360 --> 04:47.560
"Dad, how dare you
speak to my sister like that?"

04:48.160 --> 04:49.600
I said, "Wow!
She was a bitch a couple of days ago,

04:49.680 --> 04:50.920
now she's your sister? Wow!"

04:55.240 --> 04:57.680
One thing now I've seen,
you know, both my daughters and wife

04:57.760 --> 04:58.920
have become like best of friends,
you know.

04:59.040 --> 05:00.440
They fit into each other's clothes,

05:00.560 --> 05:02.360
they go partying together,
they go shopping together.

05:02.520 --> 05:04.320
They cry together, they laugh together.

05:04.520 --> 05:05.680
Yeah, they even cry together!

05:06.480 --> 05:08.560
Once I came from a show,
all three of them were crying.

05:10.040 --> 05:10.800
I said, "What happened?"

05:10.920 --> 05:12.920
Apparently, one of them
had fought with their boyfriend.

05:14.240 --> 05:15.800
Not my wife, you bastards!

05:21.120 --> 05:22.560
And I was very very upset.

05:22.920 --> 05:24.920
Because at that time,
you know, another man had made

05:25.040 --> 05:26.920
three of my favorite women in life cry.

05:27.360 --> 05:30.200
And true story, I was very
very upset because at that time,

05:30.360 --> 05:32.800
I was sharing that boyfriend's
Amazon Prime password.

05:34.880 --> 05:38.400
I didn't want to miss <i>Mirzapur</i>
just because of a stupid fight, man.

05:39.040 --> 05:40.080
Thank you, friends, Atul Khatri.

05:40.160 --> 05:41.680
You've been such a fabulous audience!

05:41.880 --> 05:42.800
Thank you so much!

05:48.560 --> 05:49.880
-Mr. Atul Khatri!
-Yes, sir!

05:49.960 --> 05:51.120
Welcome to One Mic Stand.

05:51.200 --> 05:52.200
Thank you so much for having me!

05:52.320 --> 05:54.760
See, we got such a lovely
venue for you. Rooftop!

05:55.240 --> 05:56.680
Obviously, for my class, you have to get…

05:56.800 --> 05:58.160
Yeah, we have to match your class.

05:58.640 --> 05:59.480
But tell me something.

05:59.600 --> 06:02.520
You have met Faye before?
You've worked with her or something?

06:02.600 --> 06:05.280
Yeah, obviously, I've come
for one or two of her debates.

06:05.360 --> 06:09.440
But in 2018, like two years back,
she gave me an award for,

06:09.520 --> 06:12.120
like, some Best Stand-up Comedian of 2018.

06:12.200 --> 06:13.920
-It was one of these awards in Delhi.
-Yeah.

06:14.160 --> 06:15.520
So, I was a little
skeptical about the awards,

06:15.600 --> 06:17.520
but because Faye gave it to me, I think…

06:17.600 --> 06:19.040
you know,
there was some legitimacy to it.

06:19.480 --> 06:22.280
And I think it's like a complete
circle that now today, I'm mentoring her.

06:22.360 --> 06:24.440
Yeah, you have to mentor
her as the best comedian.

06:24.520 --> 06:25.400
So, no pressure.

06:25.480 --> 06:26.760
This is your test more than hers.

06:26.920 --> 06:27.880
-Okay.
-Let's see how it goes.

06:28.680 --> 06:29.600
Hello, hello, hello!

06:29.680 --> 06:30.960
Hi! How are you doing?

06:31.040 --> 06:31.920
Are we doing elbows?

06:32.000 --> 06:33.280
-Elbow bumps.
-Fist bump.

06:34.040 --> 06:35.640
Different ones for different people.

06:37.600 --> 06:38.800
I have a question for you.

06:38.920 --> 06:41.760
Why did you want to get mentored
by Atul Khatri, of all the people?

06:42.120 --> 06:44.000
Because all the rest of your
comedians were younger than me.

06:47.480 --> 06:49.400
So you have been watching
comedy here and there?

06:49.520 --> 06:51.000
Yes, back from like, you know,

06:51.080 --> 06:53.280
when Russell Peters
became really popular in India

06:53.360 --> 06:54.960
and, you know, even before that.

06:55.120 --> 06:58.800
And it's amazing what,
like, comedy has done in India.

06:58.880 --> 07:00.760
Have you gone out to watch
like, live stand-up comedy?

07:00.840 --> 07:01.800
-Yes.
-You and your husband, like,

07:02.000 --> 07:03.000
buy tickets and go and watch?

07:03.080 --> 07:04.440
-Buy tickets and go and watch.
-Nice.

07:04.520 --> 07:06.200
A lot of times,
date night would be, like, comedy.

07:06.280 --> 07:10.000
But we'd always be sure to
sit in like fourth or fifth row,

07:10.080 --> 07:11.200
so you don't get picked on.

07:11.320 --> 07:13.000
I did one show where there was,
I won't name,

07:13.080 --> 07:15.560
but a very senior Bollywood
actor sitting in the front row.

07:15.960 --> 07:18.600
And obviously, he was watching
our kind of stand-up for the first time.

07:19.120 --> 07:21.000
And after every joke,
he was saying "Excellent!

07:21.840 --> 07:23.680
Wow! Marvelous!"
Like, you know…

07:24.720 --> 07:25.880
-Like…
-He's used to poetry conventions.

07:25.960 --> 07:27.920
Every time he did that,
people around him were laughing.

07:28.440 --> 07:30.120
But he was so cute,
I didn't want to pull him down

07:30.200 --> 07:31.680
and say, "Sir, this is a
different kind of show…

07:31.760 --> 07:33.040
You should have done this…

07:33.120 --> 07:35.520
It's not a comedy poets
convention or anything…"

07:36.720 --> 07:38.560
So, you guys don't test
your stuff on people?

07:39.000 --> 07:39.880
We do. Open mics.

07:39.960 --> 07:42.360
So my rule is, I write in the night,
supposing I find it very funny.

07:42.480 --> 07:44.800
In the morning, I again read
it to see if it is still funny.

07:45.200 --> 07:48.160
And then I would probably run it
with my daughters and my wife or something

07:48.480 --> 07:49.920
and my wife and my relation is such that

07:50.000 --> 07:52.200
if she says it's a horrible joke,
it does best on stage!

07:52.920 --> 07:55.520
Or if she says this is the best joke,
nobody laughs also.

07:55.600 --> 07:56.720
So, this is the relation--
And my daughter.

07:56.800 --> 07:57.960
But you have a lot of like…

07:58.040 --> 08:00.440
Your life story is interesting,
how you started and where you are.

08:00.600 --> 08:02.200
And this massive shift you have made,

08:02.280 --> 08:03.600
-which is a big thing to do…
-Yeah, yeah.

08:03.680 --> 08:06.280
I don't want to say "At that age"
because that I reserve for Atul.

08:06.720 --> 08:07.560
Not for you.

08:07.640 --> 08:09.440
You know, here's the funny thing, right?

08:09.960 --> 08:13.560
In television,
I was India's youngest woman editor

08:13.840 --> 08:15.360
and then I moved to the internet

08:16.080 --> 08:17.760
and now people are saying "At that age"!

08:20.000 --> 08:23.400
And I'm like, "At what age? What age?
What age are you talking about?"

08:23.480 --> 08:25.600
It's the platform that
decides your age, actually.

08:25.680 --> 08:27.400
Here, 14-year-olds have
millions of subscribers.

08:27.480 --> 08:30.000
Yeah! So, on Instagram, I'm like old now.

08:30.080 --> 08:32.600
-The space is evolving constantly.
-Every day!

08:32.680 --> 08:33.600
-Correct.
-Yeah.

08:33.680 --> 08:36.680
And you have to keep finding
new ways to stay relevant.

08:36.960 --> 08:38.960
But I realize the common
connection of yours,

08:39.040 --> 08:40.600
is that both of you
are dog parents.

08:40.760 --> 08:42.840
And your Instagram followers
are shooting up after that.

08:42.880 --> 08:43.760
-Yeah, yeah.
-Yes.

08:43.880 --> 08:46.840
You know the funny thing is that
at least in my building,

08:47.760 --> 08:48.760
I am Pheobe's mom.

08:49.720 --> 08:51.600
Nobody knows me as me, you know.

08:51.640 --> 08:53.480
So, everybody knows me because of the dog.

08:53.640 --> 08:55.280
And so this lady was
really fond of the dog

08:55.360 --> 08:56.640
and she said,
"I want to take a photograph."

08:56.720 --> 08:58.360
And I was like okay,
so she took a photograph

08:58.440 --> 08:59.880
and I happened to be in the background.

08:59.960 --> 09:01.720
Then she came back the next day
and she said,

09:01.760 --> 09:03.520
"You are a newsreader?"

09:03.640 --> 09:04.520
I said yes.

09:04.880 --> 09:07.760
So, she said, "I sent
your photograph to my son

09:07.960 --> 09:11.600
and he said, "Hey, isn't she like,
so and so, the newsreader?"

09:11.640 --> 09:14.360
She said, "No, no, she is some
simple girl who stays in my building."

09:14.480 --> 09:16.640
-"She's Pheobe's mother."
-"She's Pheobe's mother."

09:16.880 --> 09:18.640
What does it mean, "She is a simple girl?"

09:20.000 --> 09:21.640
If I want to ask you
if you want to tell her

09:21.760 --> 09:23.640
one thing for her
performance on Saturday.

09:23.960 --> 09:27.320
Stand-up comedy around the world,
if you've seen some of the new specials

09:27.400 --> 09:29.960
of leading comedians,
you sometimes get a clap

09:30.080 --> 09:31.760
even at an emotional bit.

09:32.120 --> 09:33.960
-And that's okay in comedy.
-Yeah.

09:34.040 --> 09:35.440
It's become fairly storytelling.

09:35.520 --> 09:37.360
It's not just setup-punch, setup-punch.

09:37.480 --> 09:38.840
You can take a story.

09:39.160 --> 09:41.520
That entire story may
not have a funny thing.

09:41.640 --> 09:43.320
-It may have a nice emotional message,
-Yeah.

09:43.400 --> 09:45.200
which would maybe also
give you a standing ovation.

09:45.280 --> 09:47.120
It's not just about delivering the laughs.

09:47.240 --> 09:48.840
But now, we want to learn
something from you.

09:48.880 --> 09:50.600
Because we do a segment
called Role Reversal.

09:50.760 --> 09:52.120
And we should learn something from you.

09:52.360 --> 09:55.120
So, all of the stuff I know
is all television stuff.

09:55.360 --> 09:56.520
I will teach you whatever I know.

09:56.720 --> 09:57.760
-Okay.
-It should take five minutes.

09:57.880 --> 09:59.520
That's great,
that's what we're looking for.

09:59.640 --> 10:01.000
Let's go.
Let's do this.

10:03.280 --> 10:06.200
Basically, learning how to be
a TV anchor is a three-step process.

10:06.280 --> 10:07.720
Step one is you get a jacket.

10:08.000 --> 10:09.440
Step two: You have to have your table.

10:09.520 --> 10:12.200
I like to also… have pens.

10:12.880 --> 10:14.520
-You can never have too many pens.
-So many!

10:14.880 --> 10:17.240
When you show emotion,
you might lose your pen.

10:17.320 --> 10:18.520
You have to always have another one.

10:18.600 --> 10:20.840
Depending on how you deliver news,

10:21.440 --> 10:23.000
-anything can be news.
-Okay.

10:23.080 --> 10:27.160
So say, for example,
we say that a local couple

10:27.880 --> 10:30.480
have decided to call
themselves COVID positive,

10:31.000 --> 10:34.240
