You look very chilled out
for somebody who's

12:54.960 --> 12:56.600
doing stand-up for the first time.

12:56.680 --> 12:58.400
No! So, this is me, right?

12:58.480 --> 13:00.600
-This is like me before an exam.
-Yeah.

13:00.680 --> 13:02.600
I will do whatever I can
do and then after that,

13:02.680 --> 13:04.120
dude, I can't do more than this.

13:04.200 --> 13:05.480
-Now, it's like, whatever.
-Right. Good.

13:05.560 --> 13:07.360
So, I'm in that space now, which is

13:07.440 --> 13:08.680
I've done whatever.

13:09.000 --> 13:11.720
I can't do anymore
"by-heartings" than this.

13:12.640 --> 13:14.160
I mean, this is me.
So, I'm not one of those people

13:14.240 --> 13:16.200
who get like completely psyched.

13:16.520 --> 13:19.600
I'm one of those who has
slow breakfast on exam day.

13:23.120 --> 13:24.880
See, the main reason we do this show

13:24.960 --> 13:26.480
is so that we get really popular people

13:26.800 --> 13:28.960
and see them be really scared
before the show.

13:29.080 --> 13:31.240
That's the joy of seeing how she'll panic

13:31.400 --> 13:32.600
and she's not scared at all.

13:34.520 --> 13:37.880
As I keep saying,
hold the mic like you eat a banana.

13:38.160 --> 13:39.880
Why does that sound wrong to me?

13:39.960 --> 13:42.880
It does, but it also makes
sense once you start using it.

13:42.960 --> 13:44.480
Okay. This is the banana.

13:44.640 --> 13:46.640
-At one point, if I choose,
-Yes?

13:46.720 --> 13:48.080
-can I sit on the stool?
-Of course!

13:48.160 --> 13:49.680
Wow, you're adding theatrics to this?

13:51.800 --> 13:53.120
Where is my spotlight?

13:53.200 --> 13:54.680
Give her a spotlight, please.

13:55.280 --> 13:56.160
That's it.

13:57.240 --> 14:00.040
He who laughs at himself
never runs out of things to laugh at.

14:00.120 --> 14:00.960
-See?
-Aw!

14:01.080 --> 14:03.040
That's a useful thing to remember.

14:03.840 --> 14:05.920
People in my team would be really proud,

14:06.000 --> 14:08.240
because I'm otherwise grumpy and serious.

14:08.320 --> 14:10.960
So, it'll be a different
side of me to sort of show people.

14:19.760 --> 14:23.560
I realized that Indian
dads love watching TV news.

14:23.920 --> 14:24.800
Yeah?

14:24.880 --> 14:25.880
They love watching it.

14:26.960 --> 14:27.880
All the time!

14:28.160 --> 14:29.400
Like, I'm binge-watching <i>Mirzapur,</i>

14:29.480 --> 14:31.080
my dad is binge-watching Aaj Tak.

14:32.440 --> 14:34.840
My dad watches the news
the entire day, dude!

14:35.120 --> 14:37.760
I think he thinks that
a 24-hour news channel means

14:37.840 --> 14:39.760
he has to literally watch it for 24 hours.

14:41.240 --> 14:42.160
Full day!

14:43.200 --> 14:45.200
He thinks if he stops watching,
they will stop talking!

14:47.080 --> 14:48.200
He'll watch the news all day.

14:48.280 --> 14:50.160
Next day morning, 7:00 am, newspaper.

14:51.120 --> 14:53.440
I was like, "Dad, they've printed
the same things you watched yesterday."

14:53.920 --> 14:55.200
He's like, "Yeah. It's called revision."

14:59.000 --> 15:01.600
And earlier, to become a news anchor,

15:01.680 --> 15:04.280
you needed a degree in journalism, right?

15:04.560 --> 15:06.800
Now, you need an acting course from FTII.

15:08.680 --> 15:10.920
Right? Because you
can't just deliver the news.

15:11.000 --> 15:14.760
Now you have to perform,
over-perform, exaggerate. Right?

15:14.840 --> 15:16.080
In this lockdown,

15:16.200 --> 15:18.480
something called Cyclone
Nisarga had come to Maharashtra.

15:18.840 --> 15:20.520
Thankfully, nothing much
happened in Mumbai.

15:20.600 --> 15:21.800
We all survived.

15:22.040 --> 15:24.000
But there was one journalist
standing outside the Ministry.

15:25.120 --> 15:27.840
Full overacting,
like, "Strong winds are blowing!

15:28.120 --> 15:29.680
I am not able to stand straight here.

15:29.760 --> 15:31.680
Strong winds, cyclone, storm!"

15:33.520 --> 15:35.120
There's a man picking garbage behind him!

15:36.680 --> 15:38.560
Neither that man nor the garbage
is affected by the wind!

15:39.200 --> 15:40.800
But this guy is going on and on.

15:41.520 --> 15:43.800
You know what,
compared to all this media circus,

15:44.000 --> 15:46.320
I prefer the Doordarshan news of the 90s.

15:46.720 --> 15:47.800
So much better, right?

15:47.880 --> 15:49.960
News used to come twice
a day for five minutes each.

15:50.200 --> 15:51.920
And to be a news anchor on DD News,

15:52.000 --> 15:53.320
you had to be dead inside.

15:55.560 --> 15:58.280
Right? No emotions,
no expressions whatsoever.

15:58.520 --> 16:00.920
Even Alexa has more emotions
than a DD News anchor!

16:01.760 --> 16:04.000
That man would deliver both
happy and sad news in the same tone.

16:04.080 --> 16:05.360
You wouldn't understand what is what!

16:06.040 --> 16:08.120
He's like,
"Five soldiers injured on the border.

16:08.760 --> 16:10.320
India has won the World Cup."

16:11.960 --> 16:13.120
What are you saying?

16:14.520 --> 16:17.520
Alright! Your surprise guest for tonight

16:17.920 --> 16:20.640
is one of the most powerful
voices of Indian journalism.

16:20.760 --> 16:24.120
She's a news anchor turned digital
and Instagram journalist.

16:24.360 --> 16:29.240
Please give it up for
the very cool Faye D'souza!

16:46.000 --> 16:48.400
Thank you! You are very kind.
My name is Faye D'souza.

16:48.480 --> 16:49.920
I'm doing the comedy tonight.

16:51.680 --> 16:53.120
Thank you, sir.
But that was not the joke.

16:55.200 --> 16:58.080
So, when Sapan called me
and asked me to do stand-up comedy,

16:58.160 --> 17:00.120
I was like, "Whoa!
I've never done that before."

17:00.520 --> 17:01.760
But then I was like, "I'm a TV anchor…

17:03.920 --> 17:04.840
You know?

17:06.360 --> 17:07.640
How different can it be?"

17:08.360 --> 17:09.800
But if you consider and
think about it, right?

17:09.920 --> 17:14.080
One is about stating facts,
asking the right questions,

17:14.320 --> 17:15.960
holding the government responsible.

17:17.080 --> 17:18.240
The other is TV news.

17:21.280 --> 17:23.960
So, when a male anchor puts on a suit

17:24.720 --> 17:27.240
and shouts really
loudly to make his point,

17:31.800 --> 17:35.440
people say,
"This must be the truth. Period."

17:37.040 --> 17:39.800
When I put on a suit and raise my voice,

17:39.960 --> 17:43.080
people will say, "Hmm.
She must be on her period."

17:46.720 --> 17:47.800
But now that I'm not on TV,

17:47.880 --> 17:50.440
I can share some inside
jokes with you guys.

17:50.680 --> 17:52.160
So, you know these panelists,

17:52.280 --> 17:55.040
who are opposing politicians
from opposing parties.

17:55.520 --> 17:57.160
Behind the scenes,
the things are very different.

17:58.320 --> 18:01.200
So, when the channel is on,
they're all like, "How dare you?

18:01.320 --> 18:02.800
You do not respect minorities!

18:02.920 --> 18:04.080
You do not respect women!

18:04.160 --> 18:06.160
I hate everything about your soul!"

18:06.760 --> 18:07.960
It'll go into break and they'll be like,

18:08.320 --> 18:11.960
"This saree is nice, right?
Where did you buy it from?"

18:13.440 --> 18:16.440
But I've genuinely gotten
angry a couple of times.

18:16.960 --> 18:19.440
Okay, maybe three times on my show.

18:20.000 --> 18:22.760
And I've regretted it later
because I used to call my panelists

18:22.800 --> 18:25.080
and apologize whenever
I lost my shit on air.

18:25.240 --> 18:28.560
Because I realized,
it's not fair to invite a clown

18:29.080 --> 18:31.200
and then get angry
at him for clowning, right?

18:32.560 --> 18:33.800
Why did you invite
them in the first place?

18:35.080 --> 18:38.560
You shouldn't technically shame
someone for their opinions on a show.

18:39.000 --> 18:40.320
We have Twitter for that.

18:44.280 --> 18:47.880
So, I decided that there'll
be no shouting on my show.

18:48.320 --> 18:51.080
And the people who are most
surprised by this were the panelists!

18:52.320 --> 18:53.200
This is a true story.

18:53.280 --> 18:56.480
I had one panelist
who was making a really spirited point

18:56.560 --> 18:57.440
and he stopped.

18:59.480 --> 19:02.560
He thought the video was frozen
because nobody was interrupting him!

19:09.200 --> 19:13.480
It was for all these wonderful things
that last year, I quit television news

19:14.280 --> 19:15.560
to pursue my true passion…

19:16.240 --> 19:17.160
Journalism.

19:21.560 --> 19:25.640
When I quit, a lot of people
got really concerned about me.

19:25.880 --> 19:27.320
And in the last one year,

19:28.520 --> 19:30.800
when TV news has revealed itself

19:31.240 --> 19:35.920
for the TRP-hungry,
mindless, crazy drama that it really is,

19:36.520 --> 19:38.280
I seem like a visionary now!

19:43.000 --> 19:46.920
But when I quit, I was put
on something called "Gardening leave".

19:47.640 --> 19:49.720
But for those of you who
don't know what gardening leave is,

19:49.800 --> 19:51.320
it's an HR policy.

19:51.680 --> 19:54.400
It's a notice period designed
to take you out of the game.

19:54.760 --> 19:59.080
So, you get paid your salary
but you don't go to the office.

19:59.320 --> 20:00.880
And you don't work
for anybody else either.

20:01.280 --> 20:03.320
But there's something
I wanna share with you guys

20:03.560 --> 20:07.240
that I have never spoken
about in public until now.

20:08.000 --> 20:11.880
The gardening leave was hard, right?

20:11.960 --> 20:14.680
Because I had been working
for 16 years till then.

20:14.800 --> 20:17.320
And every day at about
8:30 in the morning,

20:17.560 --> 20:19.560
when there's this beehive
activity in the building, right,

20:19.680 --> 20:20.560
in all of our buildings?

20:20.680 --> 20:21.520
People are going to work.

20:21.680 --> 20:22.880
Lunchboxes, Ola cabs…

20:22.960 --> 20:24.760
There's all this, like, buzz.

20:25.720 --> 20:28.000
I would have panic attacks.

20:28.760 --> 20:31.160
Like, I would genuinely panic.

20:31.960 --> 20:35.800
And it got worse and worse
every day until it reached a point

20:36.200 --> 20:37.760
where it became a physical pain.

20:38.280 --> 20:42.760
And that's when I realized that I
would need to get real professional help.

20:43.000 --> 20:48.320
So, I got in touch with a therapist
and I fixed my first appointment.

20:50.080 --> 20:55.520
And the doctor very sweetly said that,
"Listen, I have a backdoor.

20:55.880 --> 20:59.560
And if you wanna avoid the public gaze,
come in through the backdoor."

20:59.880 --> 21:02.040
And I thought about it and I was like,
"Public gaze?"

21:03.680 --> 21:04.520
"Me?"

21:06.080 --> 21:09.160
It's not like the paparazzi
is following me around as "Spotted!

21:10.320 --> 21:12.080
Faye D'souza in therapy look…

21:13.280 --> 21:15.240
wearing a jacket by Manish Malhotra,

21:16.160 --> 21:18.560
and eye bags by crippling anxiety!"

21:23.920 --> 21:25.080
But jokes aside,

21:25.440 --> 21:30.040
I had attached too much of my
self-esteem and my self-worth to my job.

21:30.640 --> 21:31.520
Because this is what we do.

21:31.560 --> 21:33.760
We work weekends, we work late nights.

21:34.080 --> 21:36.480
We work through personal tragedy,
we work through illness.

21:36.680 --> 21:40.080
I mean, if you were to
take leave in this country…

21:41.080 --> 21:44.800
Assume you fractured your leg
and you sent an email to HR to take leave.

21:44.920 --> 21:48.240
HR will write back saying, "Next
time, please give prior intimation.

21:48.320 --> 21:49.680
This is very last-minute.

21:52.760 --> 21:53.800
There's a client meeting."

21:54.520 --> 21:57.680
So, I decided to do one thing
that will not affect my self-esteem.

21:58.280 --> 21:59.400
I joined Instagram.

22:02.080 --> 22:05.880
But the funny thing is that in order to
be able to communicate with young people,

22:05.960 --> 22:08.080
you have to be able to
talk to them in their language.

22:08.240 --> 22:10.240
So, you can't say like--
We would say in the news,

22:10.320 --> 22:11.520
"Actress turned politician

22:11.600 --> 22:15.280
Urmila Matondkar, who unsuccessfully
contested the 2019 election

22:15.400 --> 22:17.600
has now moved from Congress to Shiv Sena."

22:18.800 --> 22:19.680
You have to say, "Bro…

22:21.960 --> 22:23.640
That Rangeela chick, Urmila, she's made…

22:29.160 --> 22:31.240
Bro, she made a
mid-season transfer, dude,

22:32.200 --> 22:33.600
from Congress to Shiv Sena."

22:39.120 --> 22:40.720
I have to check my cards because

22:41.480 --> 22:44.160
I'm not one of those journalists who
can just make shit up as they go along.

22:50.720 --> 22:53.200
For reference,
I am not an Instagram journalist.

22:53.840 --> 22:55.760
I am a journalist who
happens to be on Instagram.

22:56.600 --> 22:57.480
There is a difference.

22:58.240 --> 22:59.680
Cause when you call
me an Instagram journalist,

22:59.800 --> 23:02.200
I sound like one of
those influencers, right,

23:02.560 --> 23:05.040
who deliver news like the influencer.
"Hi, guys!

23:06.360 --> 23:07.920
It's newswoman FD.

23:08.480 --> 23:10.000
I'm dropping some truth bombs!

23:12.880 --> 23:15.080
There was a cyclone last night,
it was like woot!

23:17.480 --> 23:20.120
But don't worry,
you can get 20% off on your next vacation

23:20.200 --> 23:23.440
by using my vacation code FAYECATION!

23:23.560 --> 23:27.200
Can I get an OP Disaster in the chat?"

23:30.480 --> 23:32.040
But being on the internet is fun!

23:32.120 --> 23:35.040
When you are on television,
if you say something about another anchor,

23:35.160 --> 23:36.680
they'll slap you with a defamation suit.

23:37.920 --> 23:39.160
On YouTube, they just roast you.

23:41.320 --> 23:44.120
Like, if I were to put out a video saying,
"Sapan Verma,

23:44.280 --> 23:46.120
your jokes are so low, man,

23:46.200 --> 23:47.960
they now resemble the Indian GDP."

23:53.160 --> 23:55.880
Sapan wouldn't hit me
with a defamation suit because…

23:56.640 --> 23:58.120
Sapan cannot afford a lawyer!

24:02.160 --> 24:04.560
But honestly, I shouldn't laugh because…

24:06.280 --> 24:07.920
I can't afford anything either.

24:08.920 --> 24:10.200
Like if you've seen my videos lately,

24:10.280 --> 24:14.560
I shoot them in my living room
with the front camera of my phone.

24:15.200 --> 24:16.680
And my husband is holding the phone.

24:16.920 --> 24:18.120
So, he's my tripod.

24:18.520 --> 24:20.960
And my dog is my studio audience.

24:21.320 --> 24:23.240
And sometimes, the dog is also a panelist.

24:25.240 --> 24:26.680
But it's more authentic because

24:26.760 --> 24:29.440
I have actual dogs barking on my show!

24:35.200 --> 24:36.480
And at 9:00 p.m. every night,

24:36.560 --> 24:39.520
when I'm trying to
make a really serious point

24:41.160 --> 24:42.160
on the show

24:42.520 --> 24:44.440
the bread and eggs delivery
guy will ring the doorbell.

24:45.960 --> 24:48.520
He's taken the "Hit the bell icon"
very seriously!

24:51.880 --> 24:54.360
The downside of being on the internet…

24:55.840 --> 24:56.760
trolls!

24:57.520 --> 24:59.360
On Twitter, doesn't matter what I say,

24:59.640 --> 25:02.600
even if I post those "Flower Good Morning"

25:02.680 --> 25:04.520
WhatsApp forwards that uncles share.

25:05.400 --> 25:06.520
Even if I post that,

25:06.680 --> 25:08.720
you scroll all the way
to the bottom of the comments,

25:08.800 --> 25:11.760
and there will be these couple
of guys who'll be like, "Hindu hater."

25:12.600 --> 25:14.520
Which is hilarious,
because my husband is Hindu.

25:16.840 --> 25:18.480
So really, I'm a Hindu lover…

25:22.680 --> 25:24.680
The other thing that
gets said very regularly is,

25:25.480 --> 25:27.760
"This is too political.
I am unfollowing."

25:28.640 --> 25:29.720
So, what do you expect?

25:30.120 --> 25:31.600
It's like going to Atul Khatri's profile

25:31.680 --> 25:34.360
and saying, "Too many sex jokes.
I am unfollowing."

25:37.480 --> 25:38.920
Look at the personality, man!

25:40.800 --> 25:44.960
It's not cool to be apolitical because
politics affects everything in your life.

25:46.200 --> 25:51.520
It affects what you eat,
what you watch and who you will marry.

25:52.640 --> 25:55.320
Right? So, to say that "I'm apolitical"…

25:55.960 --> 25:58.760
is like closing your eyes
when someone is slapping you

25:58.840 --> 26:00.360
and hoping it will not hurt.

26:02.040 --> 26:04.320
Now people will argue saying,
"Fake news!"

26:05.120 --> 26:07.720
True. Fake news is dangerous.

26:07.920 --> 26:09.800
Technically, if you can spend 30 minutes

26:09.880 --> 26:13.080
trying to figure out your
Zomato order every night,

26:13.400 --> 26:17.080
you should be able to give 30 minutes
to figure out reliable sources of news.

26:17.160 --> 26:19.480
And I'll give you a hack, right?
It's a good hack.

26:21.240 --> 26:22.280
Ask yourself,

26:23.200 --> 26:26.480
"Who's paying for this news
to be produced and sent to me?"

26:27.480 --> 26:28.320
You…

26:29.640 --> 26:30.760
or the advertiser?

26:32.120 --> 26:35.400
Because whoever is paying for it is
the real customer of that service, right?

26:35.560 --> 26:37.800
If you're not paying for it,
you are not the customer.

26:37.880 --> 26:39.040
You are the commodity.

26:39.680 --> 26:45.000
Your attention span is being
chopped up into nice little packages

26:45.080 --> 26:47.000
and sold to the customer.

26:47.480 --> 26:51.000
So, you have to remember
that the choice is yours.

26:51.360 --> 26:53.440
But even if this seems like too much work,

26:53.960 --> 26:56.240
there is one thing that
you can do which is base level,

26:56.320 --> 26:58.240
very easy, to stop fake news.

26:58.600 --> 26:59.920
Don't get your news from WhatsApp.

27:05.240 --> 27:08.680
So, every time you consume news,
you get to choose

27:09.360 --> 27:13.080
whether you want facts or whether
you want sensationalism and lies.

27:13.720 --> 27:15.840
You get to choose whether
you want journalism

27:16.080 --> 27:18.800
to remain the fourth
pillar of our democracy

27:19.120 --> 27:21.600
or to become a courier service for hate.

27:22.440 --> 27:23.440
The choice is yours.

27:23.600 --> 27:24.480
You are the boss.

27:24.760 --> 27:25.920
And that is the truth.

27:26.280 --> 27:27.240
Period.

27:27.680 --> 27:28.600
Thank you!

27:32.120 --> 27:35.200
Give it up for Faye D'souza, everyone!

27:38.680 --> 27:40.320
That was the scariest
thing I've ever done.

27:40.400 --> 27:41.240
Really?

27:41.320 --> 27:43.760
And I've been inside
the COVID ICU of KEM hospital!

27:45.280 --> 27:46.480
But would you do stand-up again?

27:48.240 --> 27:49.520
-Yes!
-No, but…

27:49.880 --> 27:52.040
-Yeah!
-Yes!

27:53.360 --> 27:55.240
People are tired of seeing Atul, man.
How much more?

27:56.680 --> 28:01.040
And with COVID at my age,
I don't know how long…

28:01.480 --> 28:03.320
Ladies and gents,
you've been a fabulous audience.

28:03.400 --> 28:05.960
Thank you so much for coming out,
and supporting live stand-up comedy!

28:06.120 --> 28:07.120
This is One Mic Stand.

28:07.200 --> 28:09.240
Can we hear it once
again for Faye D'souza?

28:10.640 --> 28:11.960
Give it up for Atul Khatri!

28:12.840 --> 28:13.960
I'm your host, Sapan Verma.

28:14.040 --> 28:16.440
Thank you so much! Good night!
Bye-bye, see you.

28:28.920 --> 28:30.560
-Dude, so much fun!
-It's done!

28:30.840 --> 28:32.280
-Seriously, that was damn good!
-I have…

28:32.400 --> 28:34.960
so much respect
for what you guys do now.

28:35.320 --> 28:36.400
-Because it's just--
-Before, you didn't, huh?

28:36.640 --> 28:38.200
No, you know, it's not that.

28:38.320 --> 28:40.120
It just feels like okay,
you're telling jokes.

28:40.200 --> 28:42.080
-Yeah. Yeah.
-So, how hard could it be?

28:42.160 --> 28:43.640
But it's so hard, man!

28:44.040 --> 28:47.560
Just like lining it up,
remembering all the details,

28:47.760 --> 28:49.840
keeping the energy. It's a lot!

28:49.920 --> 28:51.560
It's more than what it seems like.

28:51.640 --> 28:55.560
You know, everything you
said in the sessions we did before

28:55.720 --> 28:57.160
was making sense on stage.

28:57.240 --> 28:58.440
You know, I could hear Atul's voice.

28:58.520 --> 29:01.000
It's like, when you learn to drive,
you can hear your dad's voice

29:01.080 --> 29:03.040
every time you take a right turn.
Like that.

29:03.120 --> 29:05.720
I could hear Atul's voice, "Alright.
Do this. Then make eye contact."

29:06.840 --> 29:08.680
Awesome!
Thank you so much for doing this!

29:08.760 --> 29:10.440
-Thank you!
-Thank you, Atul! Thank you, Faye!

29:10.520 --> 29:11.360
This was so much fun!
